---
description: Frontend conventions for app and component code
globs: src/app/**/*.tsx, src/components/**/*.tsx, src/modules/**/components/**
---

- Every data-driven view implements loading, empty, and error states. No exceptions.
- Data fetching happens in Server Components or via server actions — never in
  useEffect. Client-side fetching (rare) uses @tanstack/react-query.
- Forms: react-hook-form + zodResolver, submitting to a server action. Disable
  submit while pending; show inline field errors.
- Accessibility floor: semantic elements, labels on all inputs, visible focus
  states, keyboard operability, alt text. Use Radix/shadcn primitives for
  overlays and menus.
- Composition over prop drilling: if a prop passes through 2+ levels, restructure
  with children/slots or context.
- Styling uses design tokens only (bg-background, text-muted-foreground,
  rounded-lg, etc.). Never raw hex values or arbitrary one-off values.
- URL is state for filters/tabs/pagination — use nuqs, not useState.
- Images use next/image. LCP-critical images get priority.
